    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style descriptor tied to the exhibiting society of 16 British painters active primarily between 1911 and 1914, who regularly attended the informal Saturday afternoon gatherings first established by Walter Sickert in 1907 in London. Although it only lasted two years, its name is used in a broader sense to characterize a particular strain of British painting from about 1905 to 1920.</Note_Text>
